Some important Linux Command:
    - $ cd    ( change directory)
    - $ pwd   ( print working directory)
    - $ ls    ( list)
    - $ ls -latr    ( detail list)
    - $ mkdir ( make directory )
    - $ touch ( helps to create file )
    - $ echo  ( display the information )
             echo " Hello World " > abc.exe
    - $ cat   ( display the content inside file)
    - $ rm    ( remove file )
    - $ mv    ( move file and rename file)
    - $ sudo  ( become root )
    - $ rmdir ( remove directory)
    - $ history ( shows the previously used commands)
    - $ cp    ( copy file )
   
- providing privilege to access the file:   
    Note: 
        -rwx-rw-r (file privilege)      -user-group-other ( arrangement)
                r= read   -> 4 
                w= write  -> 2
                x= execute -> 1 = total sum is 7.
         - 7 is all rwx privilege. 
         - chmod g-rw [file_name]     ( g-rw means remove read and write privilege )
         - chmod g+rwx [file_name]    ( g+rwx means add read, write and execute privilege )
         - chmod 700 [file_name or directory_name]
 
 - Add User
   - command
        - $ sudo useradd [username]
        - $ sudo passwd [username]
        -$ su -username   (switch user)
        
 - change ownership:
      - $ chown owner:group [file_name]
      - $ sudo -a -G groupname
      
 - Delete Users:
      - $ sudo userdel -rf username
